          <text><![CDATA[<p><b>Refuge from Cruel Trapping Act</b></p> <p> Amends the National Wildlife Refuge System Administration Act of 1966 to prohibit the use or possession of body-gripping traps in the National Wildlife Refuge System. </p> <p>Imposes on persons who possess or use such traps in the System: (1) for a first offense, a civil fine of up to $500 for each body-gripping trap possessed or used; and (2) for subsequent offenses, a civil fine of up to $1,000 for each body-gripping trap possessed or used, imprisonment for up to 180 days, or both such a civil fine and imprisonment. </p> <p>Subjects to civil forfeiture any body-gripping traps that are possessed or used in violation of this Act, and any wildlife captured by the use of such traps, including the pelts and raw fur. </p> <p>Requires persons found to be in violation of such prohibition to pay all associated court costs. </p>]]></text>
          <actionDesc>Introduced in Senate</actionDesc>
